<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/national-museums-liverpool> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "National Museums Liverpool (NML) is a diverse group of museums and galleries. Its collections are among the most important and varied in Europe, and contain everything from Impressionist paintings and rare beetles to a lifejacket from the Titanic and artefacts from ancient Egypt. NML is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport ."@en .
